import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='u', y='v', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['v'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['u'] = pd.to_numeric(data['u'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['u'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['u'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['u'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average value of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
